Hmm, that’s going to be dependent on the specific way that things are set up in your theme — there isn’t really a universally-applicable way to override global content on a per-page basis.

Since your menu is hidden on this page, you do have one very simple workaround option: hide the entire navbar and header with CSS, and add the logo to the page using the page editor.

To hide the header on this page, you can add the following snippet to *Head HTML* under the *Advanced* section of your *Page Settings*:
```&lt;style&gt;
  .header-container-wrapper {
     display: none;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;```
If you would rather do it the more “correct” way, which would retain the sticky behavior and other styling of your header, your options start to get significantly more complicated and would likely require development support.
